import pandas as pd
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler


df = pd.read_csv(r'C:\Users\zoepo\AppData\Local\Temp\313cfb36-4b54-4f91-bfc7-f58cb1170af7_ECommerce_consumer behaviour.csv (1).zip.af7\ECommerce_consumer behaviour.csv')


print("Missing values per column:")
print(df.isnull().sum())


selected_columns = [
    'user_id', 'order_dow', 'order_hour_of_day', 
    'days_since_prior_order', 'reordered'
]
df = df[selected_columns]


customer_behavior = df.groupby('user_id').agg({
    'order_dow': lambda x: x.mode()[0],  
    'order_hour_of_day': 'mean',        
    'days_since_prior_order': 'mean',   
    'reordered': 'mean'                 
}).reset_index()

customer_behavior.columns = [
    'user_id', 'most_frequent_order_dow', 
    'average_order_hour', 'average_days_between_orders', 
    'reorder_rate'
]

features_to_normalize = [
    'average_order_hour', 'average_days_between_orders', 'reorder_rate'
]

scaler = MinMaxScaler()
customer_behavior[features_to_normalize] = scaler.fit_transform(
    customer_behavior[features_to_normalize]
)

print("Preprocessed Customer Behavior Data:")
print(customer_behavior.head())

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

features = customer_behavior[['average_order_hour', 'average_days_between_orders', 'reorder_rate']]


pca = PCA(n_components=2)  
principal_components = pca.fit_transform(features)

pca_df = pd.DataFrame(data=principal_components, columns=['Principal Component 1', 'Principal Component 2'])


pca_df['user_id'] = customer_behavior['user_id']


plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.scatter(pca_df['Principal Component 1'], pca_df['Principal Component 2'], alpha=0.5)
plt.title('PCA: Customer Behavior Patterns')
plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')
plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')
plt.show()


explained_variance = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
print(f"Explained variance by components: {explained_variance}")

Explained variance by components: [0.52288276 0.34687825]
In [ ]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans


kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=42)  
pca_df['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(principal_components)


plt.scatter(pca_df['Principal Component 1'], pca_df['Principal Component 2'], c=pca_df['Cluster'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
plt.title('Customer Clusters')
plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')
plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')
plt.show()
